Introduction

ATEEZ is an eight-member South Korean boy group under KQ Entertainment.

Known as KQ Fellaz at that time, ATEEZ made their first appearance in 2017 when all members auditioned for JTBC and YG Entertainment's survival show MIXNINE. Out of the eight members, four of them, Hongjoong, Mingi, Wooyoung, and Jongho, were able to pass and compete in the show, eventually being eliminated after ranking 42nd, 113rd, 132nd, and 43rd respectively.

In 2018, they gained attention by releasing pre-debut contents, notably a reality/documentary show called "KQ Fellaz American Training", which followed the group during their trainee time in Los Angeles. During the show, they wrote and choreographed the song "From", along a ninth trainee called Lee Junyoung. The song ended up being released on July 3, 2018 for the final episode of their series.

At that time, they also released three performance videos, showcasing the members abilities in dance, on May 18, May 25, and June 8, 2018 respectively. The third video only featured member Yunho. Throught this release, it was confirmed that KQ Fellaz will only have eight members.

Their group name was revealed on July 3, 2018 with a teaser for another pre-debut content called "Code Name is ATEEZ". The group name originally meant 'ATEEnager Z' but was eventually changed for just 'A to Z'.

ATEEZ started releasing teasers for their debut on October 2, 2018, and officially debuted on October 24, 2018, with the release of their first mini album titled "TREASURE EP.1: All to Zero".

On November 17, 2018, during a live, they announced their fandom name to be 'ATINY', which is a combination of 'ATEEZ' and the word 'destiny', and means that ATEEZ's future is with their fans.

On July 8, 2019, they signed with USA record label RCA Records. The same year, on November 10, they signed with Japanese record label Nippon Columbia.

ATEEZ made their Japanese debut on December 4, 2019 with the release of the album "Treasure EP. EXTRA: Shift The Map".

On December 6, 2020, San performed a special collaboration stage at the 2020 MAMA, which announced the line-up for MNET's upcoming survival show "Kingdom: Legendary War". The show took place from April 1 to June 3, 2021 and ATEEZ, who participated with seven members due to Mingi's hiatus, ended up ranking 3rd place in the finale.

On January 17, the line-up for Coachella 2024 was released with ATEEZ being part of it. They performed as headliner on April 12 and 19, 2024. This achievement makes them the first Korean boy group to take the stage at Coachella.

From April 10 to June 10, 2024, ATEEZ was featured in the GRAMMY Museum's K-pop pop-up display, where we could see various props being exposed.
